III. The Resilience Test Lab — Chaos Engineering on Your MacBook
You convert your MacBook Air into a DORA‑aligned Resilience Test Lab.

Chaos Engineering Scenario:
You intentionally disable a non‑critical security service (safe, controlled) to test whether your Python‑based Automated Recovery Logic responds correctly.

You document:
Trigger Event: What failed

Detection Logic: How your script recognized the failure

Automated Response: Restart, isolate, or reconfigure

Recovery Time: Seconds to full restoration

Post‑Recovery Validation: Ensuring the system is stable

This mirrors the resilience testing expected of EU financial institutions — but executed at the endpoint level.

Portfolio Narrative Line:
“I conducted controlled chaos experiments to validate automated recovery logic aligned with DORA Article 28.”

This positions you as someone who tests resilience, not trusts it.

